Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula has pumped the brakes on further extensions to the current driver's licence renewal deadline. More than half a million licences still need to be processed before the end of the month. OUTA's Chief Legal Officer Stefanie Fick discusses. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA  JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Fikile Mabalula might be forced to extend the current driver's licence renewal deadline. That is the view of OUTA's legal officer Stefanie Fick. She says the Minister should start thinking about extending the licence renewal period to ten years instead of five to avoid backlogs. READ: Driving Licences | WATCH | Backlog won't be an issue - Mbalula Mbalula has pumped the brakes on further extensions to the current driver's licence renewal deadline. Over 500,000 licences still need to be processed before the end of March. Watch the video above for more details on this story.  